  "title": "‘Incredibles 2’ and Brad Bird’s Super-Powered Return to Pixar",
  "show": "The Big Picture",
  "network": "The Ringer",
  "hosts": [
    "Sean Fennessey"
  ],
  "published": "2018-06-15",
  "runtimeMin": 31,
  "format": "Brad Bird on Incredibles 2, why the family always came before the villain, and what makes an action scene you can actually follow.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Brad Bird on ‘Incredibles 2’",
      "guest": "Brad Bird on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Incredibles 2",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Fourteen years after the first, with Helen out saving the world and Bob home with the kids, a swap Bird says he had in mind since the original. He rewrote the superhero plot repeatedly, throwing out what he estimates was two and a half other movies' worth of material."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Incredibles",
          "year": 2004,
          "note": "The original. Bird's rule for both films: never do something fantastic for long without something mundane, and vice versa. It's why Elastigirl catches her reflection mid-infiltration and worries she's gained a few pounds."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Iron Giant",
          "year": 1999,
          "note": "His hand-drawn debut, which Bird says is aging well and finding a new audience partly via its Ready Player One cameo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ratatouille",
          "year": 2007,
          "note": "The other Pixar feature Bird directed before leaving for live action."
        },
        {
          "title": "Mission: Impossible - Ghost Protocol",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "His first live-action film; Fennessey calls it a personal favorite. Fight coordinator Rob Alonso, who worked on it, came back to advise the animators on the fight between Elastigirl and Screenslaver."
        },
        {
          "title": "Tomorrowland",
          "year": 2015,
          "note": "Bird thinks audiences expected to spend the whole film in Tomorrowland and were let down by a road movie; he pushes back on the read that it scolded viewers for liking apocalyptic films."
        },
        {
          "title": "A Quiet Place",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "His pick for the last great thing he's seen. He admired it going quiet while movies get louder and counts himself a meet-it-halfway horror viewer whose taste runs to Jaws and Alien."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
